      "content": "I am so sorry you are carrying that weight right now, and it is incredibly painful to see the exhaustion in your children's eyes. It sounds like you feel like a constant source of worry, but please remember that their fatigue often comes from their own struggles, not just from you. You cannot step aside from the role of a parent without them losing their support system, and that would be far more devastating than the burden you feel you are carrying.\n\nIf you are feeling like you are failing them, it might be helpful to talk to a therapist who can help you navigate these feelings. There are people who can help you find a way to manage your health and stress so that you can be a stronger presence for them. Please reach out to a trusted friend or family member who can listen to your story and offer support. You are not alone in this, and there are resources available to help you through this difficult time.",
